1
00:00:07,220 --> 00:00:10,300
=Dungeon Unlocking=

2
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:11,260
(Welcome)

3
00:00:11,260 --> 00:00:13,260
(to Skill Card Redemption Center)

4
00:00:13,280 --> 00:00:15,640
In Case 3:

5
00:00:15,640 --> 00:00:16,920
Ghost Stories of Tui City,

6
00:00:16,920 --> 00:00:20,120
there are six Skill Cards.

7
00:00:21,080 --> 00:00:22,720
That sounds terrifying.

8
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:24,560
(Not scared)

9
00:00:24,560 --> 00:00:26,000
Ghost stories...

10
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,680
(Already immersed in the plot)
That sounds scary.

11
00:00:28,680 --> 00:00:30,760
The horror is about to come.

12
00:00:30,820 --> 00:00:31,640
(Don't scare me)

13
00:00:31,640 --> 00:00:33,120
Then what is the first Skill Card?

14
00:00:33,120 --> 00:00:34,440
I want the Lights On Card.

15
00:00:34,440 --> 00:00:34,820
(Skill Card)

16
00:00:34,820 --> 00:00:36,120
(Transport Card)

17
00:00:36,120 --> 00:00:37,080
Transportation?

18
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:40,420
(Transport Card grants a vehicle)

19
00:00:40,420 --> 00:00:41,160
(What does that mean?)

20
00:00:41,160 --> 00:00:42,440
Oh no.

21
00:00:42,440 --> 00:00:44,040
It's a huge map.

22
00:00:44,880 --> 00:00:47,720
Yeah. We have to run around
in the ancient town.

23
00:00:47,720 --> 00:00:49,000
The second card is...

24
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:50,920
Please give me a Lights On Card.

25
00:00:51,480 --> 00:00:54,320
(Item Card)
Can summon an inter-dimensional item.

26
00:00:54,320 --> 00:00:56,080
So even if we go back in time,

27
00:00:56,080 --> 00:00:57,720
we can use modern technology.

28
00:00:59,720 --> 00:01:01,520
A Lights On Card please.

29
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,420
(Wishing hard)

30
00:01:02,500 --> 00:01:04,120
(Disguise Card changes
your appearance for three minutes)

31
00:01:04,120 --> 00:01:07,040
Changes your appearance
for three minutes.

32
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:10,000
What does that mean?

33
00:01:11,080 --> 00:01:12,200
Oh, I know.

34
00:01:13,520 --> 00:01:14,480
Perhaps we need

35
00:01:14,480 --> 00:01:16,320
to interact with boss-level NPCs.

36
00:01:16,320 --> 00:01:18,680
(Aren't I smart?)
So we can turn into someone they trust.

37
00:01:19,720 --> 00:01:20,880
This is nice.

38
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:22,680
Infiltrate the enemy.

39
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:23,920
Let's look at the next card.

40
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:25,600
Lights On Card.

41
00:01:25,600 --> 00:01:26,800
(100 pieces Lights On Card)

42
00:01:26,800 --> 00:01:29,800
(Free Card)
Grants two free chances.

43
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:32,760
If the cafeteria is free,

44
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,360
I'm getting this card.

45
00:01:34,360 --> 00:01:35,880
(All for food)
I'll fight you for this.

46
00:01:36,440 --> 00:01:38,000
Probably get a free chance
during some games.

47
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:38,900
(Meal card king has something to say)

48
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:43,160
(Invisibility Card)
Blinds dungeon NPCs for three minutes.

49
00:01:43,160 --> 00:01:45,040
Invisibility Card.

50
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:46,640
They can't see me, but I can see them.

51
00:01:46,940 --> 00:01:47,840
(It can cover my body but not my eyes)

52
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:50,000
Can we make them
disappear for three minutes?

53
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:52,640
He needs a card
that makes others invisible.

54
00:01:53,080 --> 00:01:53,480
Yes.

55
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,520
(You know me well)
Ding, you should take this.

56
00:01:54,520 --> 00:01:55,440
With this card,

57
00:01:55,440 --> 00:01:57,280
you can do solo quests.

58
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:58,400
No, thank you.

59
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,260
(That's scarier)

60
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:00,320
(Freeze Card freezes dungeon NPCs
for two minutes)

61
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:03,920
Freezes dungeon NPCs for two minutes.

62
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:05,260
(Good card)

63
00:02:05,260 --> 00:02:06,740
(I want this)

64
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,400
I want this.

65
00:02:09,400 --> 00:02:11,280
I don't think you need
to fight for this.

66
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,440
No matter which of us
gets the Freeze Card,

67
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,720
we'll freeze them together.

68
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:15,760
What if I...

69
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,600
(Solo quest?)

70
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:17,440
Yeah.

71
00:02:17,440 --> 00:02:18,640
It's a huge map.

72
00:02:18,640 --> 00:02:20,320
We might have to split up.

73
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:21,360
If you use two card

74
00:02:21,360 --> 00:02:22,640
to protect yourself,

75
00:02:22,640 --> 00:02:24,120
I won't be happy about it.

76
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:26,720
I have no choice. I'm a weakling.

77
00:02:26,720 --> 00:02:28,200
(Doesn't care about the stress)
I'm a servant.

78
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,360
The thing is...

79
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:31,880
Freeze Card is a team buff.

80
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:33,960
Invisibility Card is a individual buff.

81
00:02:33,960 --> 00:02:35,520
I don't want the Invisibility Card.

82
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,920
Because if you get it,

83
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:38,360
it means you're the one
with the individual buff

84
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,560
and have to do solo quests for the team.

85
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:43,600
You've really thought
every little detail through.

86
00:02:44,160 --> 00:02:46,040
You must do pretty well in real life

87
00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:48,160
because no one can outsmart you.

88
00:02:48,700 --> 00:02:50,100
(Everyone here is so smart)

89
00:02:52,040 --> 00:02:54,160
Alright. Who will pick first?

90
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:55,280
Let Ning go first.

91
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,840
He has two Golden Keys.

92
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,520
Does that mean whoever
picks Invisibility Card and Freeze Card

93
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:01,320
(I want to be the boss)
is the real MVP?

94
00:03:01,380 --> 00:03:02,540
(Don't take it from me)

95
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,440
Alright.

96
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:06,920
I'll pick...

97
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:08,180
(Please)

98
00:03:09,820 --> 00:03:11,540
(I'm begging you)

99
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:13,760
the Freeze Card first.

100
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:16,160
Freeze Card.

101
00:03:16,640 --> 00:03:18,580
(What he feared happened)
For real?

102
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:19,120
Oh no.

103
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,440
That's the strongest card.

104
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,120
(Xin dies a little inside)
I'm done for now.

105
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:24,120
I'll pick the Freeze Card
and Invisibility Card.

106
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:25,520
(Xin is completely crushed)

107
00:03:25,520 --> 00:03:26,800
I'm completely blank.

108
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:30,200
Oh no, he took both jokers.

109
00:03:30,200 --> 00:03:31,440
He's got the ultimate combo.

110
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,260
(To put it simply:
Freeze Card and Invisibility Card)

111
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:35,200
Freeze Card. Invisibility Card.

112
00:03:35,200 --> 00:03:35,980
(Invisibility Card blinds dungeon NPCs
for three minutes.)

113
00:03:35,980 --> 00:03:36,840
(Freeze Card freezes dungeon NPCs
for two minutes)

114
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:38,640
Can I summon a tank

115
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,800
and hide inside?

116
00:03:40,480 --> 00:03:42,240
Yeah. You can use the Item Card.

117
00:03:42,240 --> 00:03:42,560
Yes.

118
00:03:42,560 --> 00:03:44,200
Just summon a torchlight.

119
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:45,120
You'd be unstoppable.

120
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:45,920
Yeah.

121
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:46,880
You have nothing to fear.

122
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:47,480
I'm still scared.

123
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:49,180
(A man who believes in the light)
There's no light behind me.

124
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:50,360
Listen to me, Ding.

125
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,520
With a torchlight,

126
00:03:51,520 --> 00:03:52,160
sometimes it's...

127
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,240
I can see even clearer.

128
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:53,840
Yeah.

129
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:54,840
If you shine it at...

130
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:57,060
(Is that right?)

131
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:58,720
Torchlight?

132
00:03:58,720 --> 00:03:59,240
Wait. No.

133
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,920
A torchlight with a stun gun.

134
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,120
(Xin only has one wish)
I want a high-powered torchlight.

135
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,240
Item Card.

136
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,160
(Item Card can summon
an inter-dimensional item)

137
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,400
I'll take the Transport Card.

138
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,200
It'd be even better

139
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:10,880
(Don't leave us behind)
if the vehicle can carry the whole team.

140
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,800
Just get her a bus.

141
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:14,080
Who's got a ticket?

142
00:04:15,980 --> 00:04:17,620
(Is it too late to get one now?)

143
00:04:18,070 --> 00:04:19,360
Who has a driver's license?

144
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,740
(Desperately need a chauffeur)
Yeah. We don't know how to drive it.

145
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:22,200
It won't be a car.

146
00:04:22,640 --> 00:04:23,880
Transport Card.

147
00:04:23,880 --> 00:04:25,240
(Transport Card grants a vehicle)

148
00:04:25,240 --> 00:04:26,600
Do this and use the Transport Card.

149
00:04:26,600 --> 00:04:27,480
Then get a horse.

150
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,320
I'll do this.

151
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,560
I want to use the Transport Card.

152
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:32,600
Yeah. Look.

153
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,640
I'll use the Transport Card like this.

154
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:37,200
Do I still have any other options
to choose from?

155
00:04:37,200 --> 00:04:38,100
(Jin Jing: Transport Card,
Ding Chengxin: Item Card)

156
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:38,960
(Liu Yuning: Invisibility Card
& Freeze Card)

157
00:04:38,960 --> 00:04:40,160
(Disguise Card. Free Card)
Disguise and Free.

158
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:40,920
Okay.

159
00:04:40,920 --> 00:04:43,240
With Disguise, you can ask the murderer

160
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,600
(Will probably need the Truth Card)
if it was them.

161
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:47,200
I guess I'll have
to pick the Disguise Card.

162
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:49,160
Disguise Card.

163
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:50,060
(Disguise Card changes
your appearance for three minutes)

164
00:04:50,520 --> 00:04:50,920
Like this.

165
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,900
As Player He disconnected unexpectedly,

166
00:04:56,900 --> 00:04:57,480
(Player He disconnected unexpectedly)

167
00:04:57,480 --> 00:05:00,240
the System has assigned the Free Card.

168
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:01,020
(Free Card grants two free chances)

169
00:05:01,360 --> 00:05:04,440
(Yang Chaoyue, Case 3 limited-time player)
Limited-time player, Yang Chaoyue, joining.

170
00:05:04,440 --> 00:05:06,320
(Reset Card)
System has randomly assigned a Skill Card.

171
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,340
(Restores a designated area to the state
it was in five minutes earlier)

172
00:05:08,520 --> 00:05:11,280
My Skill Card is the Reset Card.

173
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:14,680
It restores a designated area
to how it was five minutes ago.

174
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,640
Skill Cards loaded.

175
00:05:16,640 --> 00:05:17,580
(Skill Cards loaded)

176
00:05:18,460 --> 00:05:20,860
(Loading)

177
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:24,560
(Truth Inn)
Tui City is at the crossroads of the kingdoms.

178
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,920
(Zuixian Inn)
The city lord, Tui Zhuangzhu,

179
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,440
led Chivalry Manor to open its granaries

180
00:05:29,440 --> 00:05:31,400
(Chivalry Manor)
to save the people.

181
00:05:31,400 --> 00:05:33,080
But the peace didn't last.

182
00:05:33,080 --> 00:05:34,720
Once night falls,

183
00:05:34,720 --> 00:05:36,240
ghost soldiers march through the city.

184
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,160
Shadowy figures

185
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,640
and eerie apparitions appear everywhere.

186
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:42,260
(The case's detectives: Ning Waver)
Year 260 of Tui,

187
00:05:42,260 --> 00:05:44,240
(Jin Thrifty)
afternoon of 27th May,

188
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,000
(Ding Pillar)

189
00:05:45,000 --> 00:05:47,240
(Ke Stubborn)
heroes across the world gather at Tui City

190
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,600
(Yang Glory)
for the Blade Gala,

191
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:53,080
hoping to witness
the legendary Qide Sword.

192
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:53,920
Wait!

193
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,120
But unexpectedly,

194
00:05:55,120 --> 00:05:57,220
(The case's detective, He Ha)
the fortune teller, He Ha,

195
00:05:57,220 --> 00:05:58,480
arrived without warning,

196
00:05:58,480 --> 00:06:00,800
claiming that Tui Zhuangzhu
and Ning Waver

197
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:03,000
have died by the Qide Sword.

198
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,280
Did Ning Waver come back to life?

199
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,480
But why has Ning Waver

200
00:06:09,480 --> 00:06:12,040
appeared at the Blade Gala?

201
00:06:13,520 --> 00:06:17,080
And why is Qide Sword
in Jin Thrifty's hands?

202
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:22,440
Is the legend of ghost soldiers true?

203
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:27,480
Door of Truth Dungeon 3 unlocking.

204
00:06:27,480 --> 00:06:28,620
=Case Five:
Will we find the Qide Sword?=

205
00:06:28,860 --> 00:06:29,780
(Players have logged in)

206
00:06:29,780 --> 00:06:30,420
(Ding Pillar, Ning Waver, Jin Thrifty)

207
00:06:30,420 --> 00:06:31,220
(Yang Glory, He Ha, Ke Stubborn)

208
00:06:31,220 --> 00:06:31,900
(Player log)

209
00:06:32,340 --> 00:06:32,940
(Ning Waver, detective. Stamina: 180)

210
00:06:32,940 --> 00:06:33,510
(Profile. Name: Ning Waver. Age: 24)

211
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:34,170
(Identity: Tui Zhuangzhu's godson.
Occupation: Heir of Chivalry Manor)

212
00:06:34,180 --> 00:06:34,900
(Skill Card: Restore Card, Freeze Card,
Invisibility Card, Compliment Card)

213
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:37,560
(Memories erased. Ning Waver is confused.
Innkeeper, is the Blade Gala here?

214
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,520
I've lost my memory.

215
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:40,300
(Confidential)

216
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:42,320
Are you talking about me?

217
00:06:42,840 --> 00:06:43,320
Yes.

218
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:44,420
No way.

219
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,680
(Hold on. I don't believe it)
That's impossible.

220
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,720
Why are you scolding me?

221
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,920
(Let's see what this is all about)
Let's hear what else you people call me.

222
00:06:49,920 --> 00:06:52,000
(I'm not taking the blame)
It's my fault that your buns are horrible?

223
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,240
I don't remember it.

224
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:55,920
What did I do to deserve this?

225
00:06:55,920 --> 00:06:56,800
Pig.

226
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:57,240
Dog.

227
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:00,120
Not being arrogant, alright?

228
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:00,840
(Stuck on one word)
You know.

229
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,720
(Swagger king)
Like a real king.

230
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,920
(The greatest leg)
People call me the greatest leg.

231
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:05,480
At your service.

232
00:07:05,480 --> 00:07:08,600
Why does it feel like I'm
about to be the groom?

233
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,360
You watch people bath
and sleep at night.

234
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,440
Aren't you handsome?

235
00:07:12,440 --> 00:07:13,040
Yes.

236
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,480
(It just slipped out)

237
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,880
(Hang on)
I'm too much.

238
00:07:15,880 --> 00:07:17,620
I ordered you to leave.

239
00:07:17,620 --> 00:07:18,260
(Can't hold it in)

240
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:19,840
Stop swinging your arms around.

241
00:07:19,840 --> 00:07:21,800
Does your family do engravings
on grains?

242
00:07:22,360 --> 00:07:23,440
Engraving on grain?

243
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,200
He was hurt by Qide Sword.

244
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:26,980
(Ning immediately finds the evidence)
There's only one wound.

245
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:27,960
That makes it very suspicious.

246
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:28,760
Is there a possibility

247
00:07:28,760 --> 00:07:31,040
that the sword is fake?

248
00:07:31,040 --> 00:07:32,400
I think you're the prime suspect.

249
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,080
Because you're the one
who held this gala.

250
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,200
Mr. Tui might...

251
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:37,260
(Confidential)

252
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:38,400
He was killed.

253
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:41,400
So this might be a secret room.

254
00:07:41,400 --> 00:07:43,680
Where did you check my wounds?

255
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,560
What wound did you find?

256
00:07:44,560 --> 00:07:46,600
This has blood.
He might have been killed.

257
00:07:46,600 --> 00:07:48,440
But when we entered,

258
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:49,600
the floor was...

259
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,440
(Confidential)

260
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:51,840
The murderer might have exited
from there

261
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:52,420
because he used...

262
00:07:52,420 --> 00:07:52,880
(Confidential)

263
00:07:52,880 --> 00:07:56,360
Those who know Chivalry Manor
might know...

264
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:57,480
(Confidential)

265
00:07:57,480 --> 00:07:58,320
Yes.

266
00:07:58,320 --> 00:08:00,800
But outsiders don't know that.

267
00:08:00,800 --> 00:08:02,000
(Confidential)

268
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:02,480
Yeah.

269
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:04,880
So there's one last question.

270
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,400
The murderer couldn't have
left from here

271
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,560
because he wouldn't
be able to open the door.

272
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:09,140
(Can Ning Waver uncover the secret
behind the locked-room murder?)

273
00:08:09,540 --> 00:08:09,980
(He Ha, Detective,
Personal Stamina Points: 0)

274
00:08:09,980 --> 00:08:10,680
(Profile, Name: He Ha, Age: 21)

275
00:08:10,680 --> 00:08:11,400
(Identity: Unknown,
Occupation: Wandering Fortune Teller)

276
00:08:11,410 --> 00:08:11,940
(Skill Cards, Rewind Card,
Item Card, Copy Card)

277
00:08:11,940 --> 00:08:12,140
(Free Card, Singing Card, Freeze Card)

278
00:08:12,160 --> 00:08:13,560
(He Ha, a restrained fortune teller)
I'm telling you all.

279
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,080
Today's Blade Gala should be called off!

280
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:20,960
(Imposing confidence)
I am the renowned fortune teller.

281
00:08:23,520 --> 00:08:25,480
Wait. Why is everyone in such a hurry?

282
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:26,760
Line up.

283
00:08:26,760 --> 00:08:27,720
What is my name?

284
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,080
You're He Ha.

285
00:08:29,080 --> 00:08:30,360
Control your emotions.

286
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,160
Let me be clear.

287
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:33,120
Today, I am the detective.

288
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,950
When you see me,
you'd better show some respect.

289
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,480
Where's your musket?

290
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,400
I didn't bring it.

291
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,800
Then why don't you go in first?

292
00:08:39,800 --> 00:08:40,800
We'll follow after you.

293
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,120
I'm not sure I can get it open.

294
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:42,800
Can you see anything?

295
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:43,760
My vision is perfectly clear.

296
00:08:45,640 --> 00:08:48,880
The killer's intentions
are written all over this scene.

297
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:50,120
Take it off and let us have a look.

298
00:08:50,120 --> 00:08:52,520
You show us this and say

299
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,720
we're all illiterate.

300
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:54,240
Exactly.

301
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,880
We uncovered three crucial clues.

302
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:58,320
(Decisive move, Battle of logic)
Let's see how innocent you really are.

303
00:08:58,320 --> 00:09:00,160
Who painted this portrait?

304
00:09:00,160 --> 00:09:02,440
And upon whom did you cast
your dark sorcery?

305
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,060
(Confidential)

306
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:03,640
Is he alive?

307
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:05,120
Let's look at the killer's perspective.

308
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:06,520
Something must be inside Chivalry Manor

309
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,800
that they desperately wanted.

310
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:10,160
No, those shoes belonged to...

311
00:09:10,160 --> 00:09:10,920
that person...

312
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:11,580
(Confidential)

313
00:09:11,760 --> 00:09:12,520
who wears it.

314
00:09:13,520 --> 00:09:14,160
He was killed by...

315
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:14,740
(Confidential)

316
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:15,400
him.

317
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,120
Could've been a body swap

318
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:18,720
or perhaps he was carrying...

319
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:19,540
(Confidential)

320
00:09:20,360 --> 00:09:22,640
Which means the door
had to be shut because...

321
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:23,880
(Confidential)

322
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,280
The killer never...

323
00:09:25,280 --> 00:09:26,040
(Confidential)

324
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,400
I just realized something.

325
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,560
That seal had been reapplied.

326
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,600
(Confidential)
Everything he did afterward...

327
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:34,840
was completely out of character.

328
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:38,220
(Can He Ha identify the true killer?)

329
00:09:38,660 --> 00:09:39,260
(Jin Thrifty,
Personal Stamina Points: 100)

330
00:09:39,260 --> 00:09:39,950
(Profile, Name: Jin Thrifty, Age: 21)

331
00:09:39,950 --> 00:09:40,570
(Identity: Unknown,
Occupation: Proprietress of Truth Inn)

332
00:09:40,570 --> 00:09:41,220
(Skill Cards: Transport Card,
Compliment Card, Rewind Card)

333
00:09:41,240 --> 00:09:45,840
(Counts every coin, living frugally)
Blade Gala shall now begin.

334
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:49,880
Everyone came for the sword.

335
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:50,520
What does that mean?

336
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,560
It doesn't sound very flattering.

337
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,440
My apologies.

338
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:54,680
I meant everyone here loves swords.

339
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:56,400
(Everyone loves swords)
I accidentally left out a word.

340
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,520
I'm also hoping to find a true hero,

341
00:09:58,520 --> 00:10:00,520
someone capable of drawing this sword

342
00:10:00,520 --> 00:10:02,260
just as he might open

343
00:10:02,260 --> 00:10:03,200
(Playful wink)
the door to my heart.

344
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,360
I'm not an easy woman to win over.

345
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,440
Then he grabbed me by the throat.

346
00:10:09,440 --> 00:10:10,800
If the day ever comes

347
00:10:10,800 --> 00:10:12,640
when I can confront him,
I'll stand my ground.

348
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:17,080
I'm a strong. A strong, foolish woman.

349
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:19,400
Wait. He has Longdong Gun.

350
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:21,280
(Next comes Jin's brilliant deductions)
Why are you so upset?

351
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,160
One moment.

352
00:10:22,160 --> 00:10:23,400
You said the two of them were dead.

353
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:24,880
You checked for their pulse yourself?

354
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:25,480
That's right.

355
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:27,160
Then tell us the truth.

356
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:29,280
When you examined the wound,

357
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,280
did you notice
the strawberry-shaped birthmark here?

358
00:10:31,280 --> 00:10:32,280
Their deaths had nothing

359
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:33,960
to do with martial prowess

360
00:10:33,960 --> 00:10:34,280
because...

361
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,280
(Confidential)

362
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:37,240
So it was the two of you all along.

363
00:10:37,740 --> 00:10:38,680
(Confidential)

364
00:10:38,680 --> 00:10:40,160
Someone put on the Black-Robed
Man's cloak...

365
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:41,280
(Confidential)

366
00:10:41,280 --> 00:10:41,680
Exactly.

367
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:42,280
That's right.

368
00:10:42,280 --> 00:10:44,760
So if they intended
to fabricate an alibi,

369
00:10:44,760 --> 00:10:47,000
there's a good chance
they planned to use me as part of it.

370
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:49,040
Both of them had every reason

371
00:10:49,040 --> 00:10:50,640
to investigate your true identity.

372
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:52,960
The killer...

373
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:54,040
(Confidential)

374
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:55,000
Perhaps at that moment...

375
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,280
(Confidential)
He had no choice.

376
00:10:56,280 --> 00:10:59,720
Every one of your movements that night

377
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,440
caught me completely off guard.

378
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:04,040
If he had picked up this letter,

379
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,240
he would have known...

380
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:06,600
(Confidential)

381
00:11:06,600 --> 00:11:07,400
Exactly. That's right.

382
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:07,720
Right?

383
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:09,360
Which means he completely ruled out.

384
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,340
(Who will Jin Thrifty
eliminate from suspicion?)

385
00:11:11,740 --> 00:11:12,290
(Ding Pillar,
Personal Stamina Points: 200)

386
00:11:12,290 --> 00:11:12,890
(Profile, Name: Ding Pillar, Age: 21)

387
00:11:12,890 --> 00:11:13,500
(Identity: Unknown,
Occupation: Waiter at Truth Inn)

388
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:14,340
(Skill Cards: Hint Card, Item Card,
Massage Card ×2, Dancing Card)

389
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,360
Then what am I supposed to do?

390
00:11:15,360 --> 00:11:16,520
(Chivalry makes one stand tall)

391
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:17,680
But I'm still just a child.

392
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:18,960
And who exactly are you?

393
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,440
I'm young Martial Artist.

394
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:22,500
(Poke)

395
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,600
You have ulterior motives.

396
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,400
Mr. Ke, she...

397
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,720
Detective, please.

398
00:11:26,720 --> 00:11:29,240
(Young Martial Artist shows his talent)
Let this self-taught prodigy, handle it.

399
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,640
How impressive.

400
00:11:32,720 --> 00:11:34,400
A true hero always
puts the world before himself.

401
00:11:34,400 --> 00:11:36,560
A true hero speaks
for the common people.

402
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,920
Your path of chivalry
is yours alone to discover.

403
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:41,600
Why do you expect
everyone else to find it for you?

404
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:42,480
You're far too lazy.

405
00:11:45,120 --> 00:11:46,640
Now that I've found him.
I'm no longer afraid.

406
00:11:48,860 --> 00:11:51,140
(Don't look at me)

407
00:11:52,680 --> 00:11:54,640
No need. I'll just look for the doll.

408
00:11:54,640 --> 00:11:55,400
I'll find it.

409
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,520
I wanted to see
whether the Qide Sword was inside.

410
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:58,520
It wasn't.

411
00:11:58,520 --> 00:12:00,360
(Ding digs deep into every detail)
Isn't this the body?

412
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:00,600
Because...

413
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,440
(Confidential)

414
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:03,400
You should be the one who killed him.

415
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:04,400
Wait.

416
00:12:04,920 --> 00:12:05,520
What?

417
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,680
It was locked from the outside?

418
00:12:07,700 --> 00:12:08,780
(Confidential)

419
00:12:08,880 --> 00:12:09,400
Knocked out.

420
00:12:09,400 --> 00:12:09,880
That's right.

421
00:12:09,880 --> 00:12:12,000
I think it was an ambush.

422
00:12:12,000 --> 00:12:13,360
There's also...

423
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,600
See? Look.

424
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:16,480
Look.

425
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:17,680
Why was this crossed out?

426
00:12:17,680 --> 00:12:19,200
If we follow the killer's logic,

427
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:21,520
he would have been in a hurry
to reach his next victim.

428
00:12:21,520 --> 00:12:23,320
In my opinion,

429
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,000
that would mean...

430
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:25,640
(Confidential)

431
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:27,480
But he approached you at the same time.

432
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:28,880
(Confidential)

433
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,160
Then he fought Tui Zhuangzhu.

434
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,560
Here's what I think.

435
00:12:31,560 --> 00:12:33,760
(Confidential)
He met the person leaving.

436
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,680
I was the one entering.

437
00:12:34,680 --> 00:12:35,280
Exactly.

438
00:12:35,280 --> 00:12:36,520
I think someone much closer to him

439
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:37,880
would have helped him accomplish it.

440
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:40,420
(Can Ding Pillar
clear himself of suspicion?)

441
00:12:40,860 --> 00:12:41,380
(Ke Stubborn,
Personal Stamina Points: 0)

442
00:12:41,380 --> 00:12:42,220
(Profile, Name: Ke Stubborn, Age: 22)

443
00:12:42,220 --> 00:12:42,400
(Identity: Unknown)

444
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:42,820
(Occupation: Junior Disciple
of a Prestigious Sect)

445
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:43,420
(Skill Cards: Disguise Card,
Rewind Card)

446
00:12:43,540 --> 00:12:45,020
(The Wandering Swordsman, Ke Stubborn)

447
00:12:45,020 --> 00:12:45,680
(Theatrically controls
his sword by hand)

448
00:12:45,680 --> 00:12:46,880
Hero, you look rather disheveled.

449
00:12:48,260 --> 00:12:49,460
(Come on. Show us)

450
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,080
These two swords are called

451
00:12:53,640 --> 00:12:55,920
the Moonlight Toothpick Swords.

452
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:56,560
Toothpick?

453
00:12:56,560 --> 00:12:59,400
Are they meant for picking
your teeth after a meal?

454
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:03,560
Good thing I didn't eat
those steamed buns.

455
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,720
Even the food safety
at this inn is questionable.

456
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:07,520
Take it off.

457
00:13:07,520 --> 00:13:09,600
Should I lead the way, everyone?

458
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,160
(Only Fearless Scout)
Yes. You're the one who has to go first.

459
00:13:11,160 --> 00:13:13,040
I'll give you the shoes.
What will you give us in return?

460
00:13:13,400 --> 00:13:15,640
You'll earn a word of praise from me.

461
00:13:15,640 --> 00:13:16,440
Don't give him the shoes.

462
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,720
I'd rather eat them myself.

463
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:20,600
You're reading it
like we're all illiterate.

464
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:22,120
I'd advise you to tell the truth,

465
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:23,240
killer.

466
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:23,700
(Not ruling out any possibility)

467
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:26,560
The true master of poison
and hidden weapons has appeared.

468
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:29,120
That explains why he acted
the way he did.

469
00:13:29,120 --> 00:13:30,200
But that raises another question.

470
00:13:31,080 --> 00:13:32,600
There are two possibilities
for the killer.

471
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:32,880
One is...

472
00:13:32,880 --> 00:13:34,420
(Confidential)

473
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:35,280
The other is...

474
00:13:35,280 --> 00:13:36,560
(Confidential)

475
00:13:36,560 --> 00:13:38,000
By the time I made that doll,

476
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,400
all of this had yet to happen.

477
00:13:40,400 --> 00:13:41,220
(Confidential)

478
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:43,160
He wanted to conceal his identity.

479
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,120
So he deliberately
made everyone believe that...

480
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:45,740
(Confidential)

481
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:46,680
That's why it's crossed out.

482
00:13:47,760 --> 00:13:49,400
After serving me the wine,

483
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,520
before the cook arrived...

484
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:51,260
(Confidential)

485
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,960
the bell had rung.

486
00:13:52,960 --> 00:13:54,800
To me, that timing

487
00:13:54,800 --> 00:13:56,320
reveals quite a lot.

488
00:13:56,320 --> 00:13:59,640
The killer came to the tavern

489
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:01,520
specifically to establish an alibi.

490
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,320
Yet he also knew

491
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:04,320
exactly what was happening over there.

492
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:05,840
Because he had to rush back...

493
00:14:05,840 --> 00:14:07,180
(Confidential)

494
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,440
Is the timeline right?

495
00:14:09,080 --> 00:14:10,200
Then he couldn't have

496
00:14:10,200 --> 00:14:12,240
stayed in this tavern that long.

497
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,600
The more airtight someone's timing is,

498
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:15,200
the more suspicious I think they are.

499
00:14:16,940 --> 00:14:19,220
(Can Ke Stubborn use
the timeline to catch the killer?)

500
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:20,190
(Yang Glory)

501
00:14:20,190 --> 00:14:21,020
(Profile Name: Yang Glory Age: 21)

502
00:14:21,020 --> 00:14:21,670
(Identity: Unknown
Job: Cook at Truth Inn)

503
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,220
(Skill Card: Reset Card)

504
00:14:22,380 --> 00:14:24,940
("Super" curious Yang Glory)

505
00:14:24,960 --> 00:14:25,840
(Good little cook)
Enjoy your meal.

506
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,040
I've had it too.

507
00:14:27,040 --> 00:14:28,200
(Blunt as ever)
It was bad, so they hired me.

508
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,200
I know. Someone's framing someone.

509
00:14:30,640 --> 00:14:32,000
Who's framing who?

510
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:33,140
(What is going on.jpg)

511
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:34,880
That's weird.

512
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,460
(Ha?)

513
00:14:38,020 --> 00:14:40,180
(Panicking.gif)

514
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:44,080
(Thinking hard)
The Venomous Duo.

515
00:14:44,080 --> 00:14:45,640
Feels like Gao Jianli barged in.

516
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,520
(Showing off her vocals)
♪For you, I became a werewolf♪

517
00:14:48,520 --> 00:14:49,320
Wait!

518
00:14:51,680 --> 00:14:52,800
I can't reach it.

519
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,360
(Pushing the limit)
Try it. Go again.

520
00:14:54,360 --> 00:14:55,400
I can't get down.

521
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:58,120
It's kinda hot.

522
00:14:58,120 --> 00:14:59,880
No one wears a headscarf.

523
00:14:59,880 --> 00:15:02,040
It's this dark. Who can see shoes?

524
00:15:02,380 --> 00:15:03,900
(If I can't see, no one can see me)

525
00:15:04,380 --> 00:15:05,320
(Manual detector)

526
00:15:05,320 --> 00:15:06,880
It kinda slipped my mind.

527
00:15:06,880 --> 00:15:09,040
During this investigation,

528
00:15:09,040 --> 00:15:10,800
("Super" sharp and clear-headed)
I found a man in black.

529
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:12,920
They were practicing dark magic.

530
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,680
Dark magic?

531
00:15:14,680 --> 00:15:16,160
Look. There's a cup here.

532
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,080
So he drank water.

533
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,680
Then why would they fight

534
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,000
with the room all closed up?

535
00:15:20,800 --> 00:15:23,880
And he's very close to that doctor.

536
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,280
So that means he used that medicine.

537
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:26,320
(Confidential)

538
